    {
      "sender": "Aaron Vontell",
      "user_id": "UCWNLU6CB",
      "message": "What’s the right way to restart our docker containers using provisioner? Do I need to run compile again?",
      "time": "06:49",
      "timestamp": "1574866179.039700",
      "is_reply": false
    },
    {
      "sender": "lydia",
      "user_id": "UJK4LKYSJ",
      "message": "if you just need to restart you can just do stop/start",
      "time": "06:49",
      "timestamp": "1574866198.039800",
      "is_reply": true
    },
    {
      "sender": "lydia",
      "user_id": "UJK4LKYSJ",
      "message": "if you need to rebuild some code or something, then you need to compile",
      "time": "06:50",
      "timestamp": "1574866207.040000",
      "is_reply": true
    },
    {
      "sender": "lydia",
      "user_id": "UJK4LKYSJ",
      "message": "but i also make an option to mount code directly into the docker container so you don't have to rebuild the containers each time code changes",
      "time": "06:50",
      "timestamp": "1574866231.040200",
      "is_reply": true
    },
    {
      "sender": "lydia",
      "user_id": "UJK4LKYSJ",
      "message": "what are you trying to do?",
      "time": "06:50",
      "timestamp": "1574866234.040400",
      "is_reply": true
    },
    {
      "sender": "Aaron Vontell",
      "user_id": "UCWNLU6CB",
      "message": "I see, yeah asking about the iteration of changing code and restarting to test those changes",
      "time": "06:50",
      "timestamp": "1574866244.040600",
      "is_reply": true
    },
    {
      "sender": "lydia",
      "user_id": "UJK4LKYSJ",
      "message": "oo yup so for that, I stop the service with provisioner",
      "time": "06:50",
      "timestamp": "1574866259.040800",
      "is_reply": true
    },
    {
      "sender": "Aaron Vontell",
      "user_id": "UCWNLU6CB",
      "message": "But whenever I run compile it redoes some things like setting up cassandra which takes so so long",
      "time": "06:51",
      "timestamp": "1574866262.041000",
      "is_reply": true
    },
    {
      "sender": "lydia",
      "user_id": "UJK4LKYSJ",
      "message": "and then start the docker manually with `make run-docker-reload`",
      "time": "06:51",
      "timestamp": "1574866277.041300",
      "is_reply": true
    },
    {
      "sender": "lydia",
      "user_id": "UJK4LKYSJ",
      "message": "you still have to run `make build-reload` everytime the code changes (outside docker) because we copy code from the src dir into build",
      "time": "06:51",
      "timestamp": "1574866298.041500",
      "is_reply": true
    },
    {
      "sender": "lydia",
      "user_id": "UJK4LKYSJ",
      "message": "but you don't have to restart the docker container",
      "time": "06:51",
      "timestamp": "1574866305.041700",
      "is_reply": true
    },
    {
      "sender": "lydia",
      "user_id": "UJK4LKYSJ",
      "message": "`make run-docker-reload` mounts the build dir into the docker container",
      "time": "06:51",
      "timestamp": "1574866319.041900",
      "is_reply": true
    },
    {
      "sender": "lydia",
      "user_id": "UJK4LKYSJ",
      "message": "you do have to stop/restart the server script (`start-worker.sh` or `start.sh` depending on what service it is",
      "time": "06:52",
      "timestamp": "1574866337.042100",
      "is_reply": true
    },
    {
      "sender": "lydia",
      "user_id": "UJK4LKYSJ",
      "message": "since our servers unfortunately don't yet hot reload",
      "time": "06:52",
      "timestamp": "1574866346.042300",
      "is_reply": true
    },
    {
      "sender": "lydia",
      "user_id": "UJK4LKYSJ",
